(1.1)Process Flow : A specification of the steps needed to manufacture a product. Traditional shop floor control is usually specified in a structured document system in which a printed copy of the process-flow specification,
	called a run-card, accompanied a wafer lots as it moved between different fabrication equipment. EQP operators follow the instructions on the run-card to process the wafer lot.
	...--> Back Side Clean --> PR coating --> Exposure --> Alignment Check --> Etch --> ...
	Top Plan(process) : One product need to be assigned to a Top Plan; Sub-Plan(Layer) : Per Photo Layer, Per Module Area has a Sub-Plan; Step : Define Physical process step, EQP Type & Recipe & Reticle & EDC Plan

